In the howling crags of Glimmerfrost, where blizzards flayed the stone and avalanches hungered for flesh, a fur-shrouded exile clambered to the igloo of Eira, a seal-speaker whose oil-lamps flickered amid polar bear prowls and rift-quakes. His breath steamed cryptic runes, eyes glacial under hood—was he storm-banished or ice-wight manifest? Eira's blubber-caches dwindled, sustaining her shivering daughter through the endless night. To seal the snow-door violated the Frost Oath of Glacira, peak-sovereign whose gales decreed: "Sojourner past hearthfire fuses as bone-kin; doom him, and glaciers grind your soul."

